Date:     Fri, 17 Feb 1995 05:13:57 -0500    
Reply-To: UB Poetics discussion group <POETICS@UBVM.CC.BUFFALO.EDU>     
Sender:   UB Poetics discussion group <POETICS@UBVM.CC.BUFFALO.EDU>     
From:     Sheila Murphy <SEMAZ@AOL.COM>      
Subject:  Thoughts on Theory  
    
Just spinning off Spencer's latest post (hi, Spencer!), I sense that much   
about theory (I fear I point to an abstraction rather than to any certain   
individual viewpoint) risks treatment as commodity, rather than as the fluid    
thing it is.  The dance of interplay between theory and practice means for me   
that there is always something to enjoy, closer to infinite ways of looking 
at a single entity.  It is as though one should not (consciously) stop, for 
fear of giving the nod to gravity and then falling for who knows how long.  
    
The pleasure of theory is certainly one of its big selling points, in   
addition to its power to locate, frame, describe, attune to resonances not  
previously picked up.     
    
Sheila Murphy  
