From:     eric pape <ENPAPE@LSUVM.SNCC.LSU.EDU>  
Subject:  Re: refried theory and deified beans   
In-Reply-To:  Message of Tue, 21 Feb 1995 08:59:45 -0500 from       
      <mboughn@EPAS.UTORONTO.CA>  
    
Has anyone here read Viswanathan's new book about the history of    
"literary" studies in India? Basic assertion that literary studies      
in English began not in England or America, still under the classical   
mode of learning, but in India where it was used to "Anglicize" Indian  
subjects, ie, the teaching of English values through English literature     
meant to "replace" their own culture, which was obviously devalued      
as "primitive."    
 My point is to suggest that if we want to historicize theory,      
a very good idea incidentally, we cannot forget to do the same      
for art, and for philosophy, and particularly not for "literary     
criticism.""Any document of civilization..." etc.    
 Thanks, Eric. 
=========================================================================   
