Just a brief reply, but I think it is a majoy misunderstanding to think     
of Adorno as a cynic. A pessimist, certainly. To some extent a paralyzed    
thinker, I grant. But not a cynic. A cynic gives in to the barbarity.   
A cynic gives up the ever more problematic possibility of Utopia.   
 Adorno had a hell of a lot of problems as a person and sometimes   
as a thinker, but he was never a cynic.   
 Thanks, Eric. 
