And expand they should. But with the usual pendulum effect, things swish far    
in one direction.  I find theory and discussion enriching at least, yet feel    
concern about any climate that would seem to dictate that a writer who is   
real, concerned, or whatever must become a full service provider of the range   
of thought services.   
    
Sometimes, when in the midst of discussion, I begin to want to find a poem. 
 Perhaps simply a bout of longing that could be dismissed as discourageable 
emotion or hunger for a different thing.  
    
Sheila     
